@jreback One of the reasons the `PeriodIndex` constructer is so convoluted is there are some odd cases supported (I imagine through many bugfixes & iterations!). One of them is a _list of ints representing years_. An array of ints are interpreted as ordinals, but a list is coerced to years within the `Period` constructor.

Here's an example: https://github.com/SixtyCapital/pandas/blob/master/pandas/tseries/tests/test_period.py#L2216

What do you think about not allowing that?
